tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE quantum_key_pairs (
    id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    public_key TEXT,
    private_key TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE communication_logs (
    log_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    timestamp TIMESTAMP,
    message TEXT,
    sender_id UUID,
    receiver_id UUID,
    FOREIGN KEY (sender_id) REFERENCES quantum_key_pairs(id),
    FOREIGN KEY (receiver_id) REFERENCES quantum_key_pairs(id)
);

CREATE TABLE communication_logs (
    log_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    key_id INT NOT NULL,
    timestamp TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    message TEXT NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (key_id) REFERENCES quantum_keys(key_id)
);

CREATE TABLE QuantumKeyPairs (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  public_key VARCHAR(255),
  private_key VARCHAR(255)
)

CREATE TABLE CommunicationLogs (
  log_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  communication_date TIMESTAMP,
  message TEXT,
  sender_id UUID,
  receiver_id UUID
)

CREATE TABLE Users (
  user_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  username VARCHAR(50),
  email VARCHAR(100)
)

CREATE TABLE Permissions (
  permission_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  permission_name VARCHAR(50)
)

CREATE TABLE communication_logs (
    log_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    communication_date TIMESTAMP,
    sender_id INT,
    receiver_id INT,
    message_text TEXT
);
